LAGOS  – Head coach of Nigeria’s women wrestling team, Purity Akuh is ‘confident’ his wards will dominate the continent at the 2020 African Wrestling Championships in Algiers, Algeria. Nigeria’s female wrestlers have won the Women Wrestling event in the last eight years, and will be hoping to extend their record in the tournament which runs from February 4 to 9. The Nigeria Wrestling Federation (NWF) has named a team of 10 female wrestlers in all available weight classes, as well as five males for the competition, which serves as a pre-Olympic qualifier. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “I am confident that we will make it nine in a row, this year will make it nine years in a row of winning the female title,” the coach told NWF Media. In Algiers, Akuh will be counting on 9-time African champion, Blessing Oborududu (68kg), five-time winners Odunayo Adekuoroe (57kg) and Aminat Adeniyi (62kg), as well as reigning champions Mercy Genesis (50kg), Sunmisola Balogun (72kg) and Blessing Onyebuchi (76kg), to rule the continent again. At the last African Championships in Hammamet, Tunisia in 2019, the Nigerian women claimed five gold, two silver and two bronze medals to emerge overall champions in Women Wrestling.